author: News Release
title: Streets Closed Friday Night For Maple Leaf
text: CARTHAGE, MISSOURI - Several sides of the Historic Carthage Square will be closed beginning Friday night at 4PM for Maple Leaf events. 4th Street between, but not including, Main St. and Grant St. will be closed for early vendor set-up in anticipation of Saturdayâ€™s festival day. In addition, the North, West, and East sides of the square will be closed for the Maple Leaf Cruise Night. Manned barricades will be in place so if you will be traveling through this portion of town on Friday night after 4 PM, please find an alternate route. For more information, 358-2373 or carthagemapleleaf.com .
